column4: Say guys, whenever I try to configure my modem, I get an error message that says "Modem is Busy."  I have the modem link directed to a TTYS#, but nothing works.
Wait, why did the last half of my message come out?
Say guys, whenever I try to configure my modem, I get an error message that says "Modem is Busy."
I'm sorry: I don't know what you mean.  I think it's dial-up.
well is it the modem that provides the internet to your computer? or are you going to use it for faxing via a normal phone line?
I'm going to use it as an Internet connection to my computer.
I should probably mention I was using KPPP.
so will it have to dial a number or does a cable tv type wire screw into the back of it?
ah.. sounds like DSL.. is that right?
It will have to dial a number.
Please don't take this the wrong way, but why are you asking me all these questions?

to determine the right kind of answers for your problem.. You didn't give enough info in the beginning to make any judgements.  There's a big difference between a DSL "modem" and a standard die-in-the-woll modem typically used for faxing.  If it's DSL, sorry I can't help.
I don't think it's DSL, but then again, I'm not sure.
I don't think it's DSL, but then again, I'm not sure.
there in lies the problem.  difficult to fix when the item is a mystery.
Can we assume I don't have DSL?
